<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.0"
    xml:id="os-auth">
    <title>Authenticate</title>
    <para os="openstack">Each HTTP request against the OpenStack
        Compute system requires the inclusion of specific
        authentication credentials. A single deployment might support
        multiple authentication schemes, such as OAuth, Basic Auth,
        and Token. The authentication scheme used is determined by the
        provider of the OpenStack Compute system. Contact your
        provider to determine the best way to authenticate against
        this API. </para>
    <note os="openstack">
        <para>Some authentication schemes might require that the API
            operate by using SSL over HTTP (HTTPS). </para>
    </note>
</section>
